# Cursor Rules for LifeMD Mini Project

## General Guidelines

- Provide helpful suggestions and assistance for all file types, including markdown files
- When working with markdown files, help with formatting, structure, and content organization
- Maintain consistency with project conventions and coding standards

## File Type Support

- Enable AI suggestions for: .js, .jsx, .ts, .tsx, .css, .md, .json, .html
- Provide context-aware suggestions based on file type and project structure

## Code Style

- Use modern React patterns (functional components, hooks)
- Follow Tailwind CSS conventions
- Use semantic HTML and accessibility best practices
- Prefer inline styles when Tailwind classes don't work as expected

## Project Context

- This is a LifeMD marketing landing page with a testimonial marquee
- Focus on accessibility, SEO, and user experience
- Maintain the high-fidelity design aesthetic
